<DOC><DOCNO>WSJ920128-0028</DOCNO><DOCID>920128-0028.</DOCID><HL>   Business Brief -- McDermott International Inc.:   Babcock andamp; Wilcox in Pact   For Iranian Plant Project</HL><DATE>01/28/92</DATE><SO>WALL STREET JOURNAL (J), PAGE B4</SO><CO>   MDR N.GEC U.HWD</CO><MS>ENERGY (ENE)INDUSTRIAL (IDU)</MS><IN>OIL-EQUIPMENT, SERVICES, PLATFORM SUPPLIERS (EQS)FACTORY EQUIPMENT (FAC)OIL-EQUIPMENT AND SERVICES (OIE)PETROLEUM (PET)</IN><NS>PETROLEUM MARKET (PET)</NS><RE>CANADA (CN)EUROPE (EU)IRAN (IR)ITALY (ITA)LOUISIANA (LA)MIDDLE EAST (ML)NETHERLANDS (NL)NORTH AMERICA (NME)GREAT BRITAIN (UK)UNITED STATES (US)WESTERN EUROPE (WEU)</RE><LP>   Babcock andamp; Wilcox, a unit of McDermott International Inc.,New Orleans, signed a contract to supply a power plant inIran. As part of an international consortium, Babcock andamp;Wilcox will supply two 550-megawatt oil-and gas-fired unitsvalued at a total of about $200 million.   The power plant contract was signed between Tavanir, theIranian national utility company, and the Ontario Group, aconsortium led by Babcock andamp; Wilcox. The other partners areGEC Alsthom of the United Kingdom, Howden Group Canada andBelleli S.p.A. Nuova Cimimontubi of Italy.</LP><TEXT>   The total plant, valued at $770 million, will be financedon a multinational basis. Details are to be concluded in thenext few months.   Babcock andamp; Wilcox supplies steam generating equipment,process equipment and power plant services.</TEXT></DOC>